Narrator

Sitting at the head of my council room table, I once again checked the time on the wall-mounted timepiece. It was fifteen past three.

Player_Romus

“It’s unusual for Lucita to keep us waiting like this.”

Narrator

Two men in military uniforms followed her, pushing a film projector into the room.

Titus Gordion

“What exactly are we looking at? Where was this footage taken?”

Narrator

The film concluded and the lights in the room were brought back up. Lucita turned to her men.

Player_Romus

“Okay, what exactly did I just watch?”

Lucita Azaro

“The exchange of some of the main components used in the bomb, identified through the serial numbers of the materials retrieved from the crime scene, courtesy of Wehlen's investigation team."

Player_Romus

“Okay, you’ve got my attention. Please go on.”

Lucita Azaro

“As I've mentioned before, the material we've been dealing with here came straight from CircuitRise Systems in Pales."

Narrator

Lucita opened her folders and handed out photos of the man.

Player_Romus

“My, my... quite the industrious individual.”

Lucita Azaro

“That’s putting it mildly.”

Player_Romus

“How did your team track his whereabouts? Or a better question... what led you to discover this footage in the first place?”

Lucita Azaro

“You see, being in a high position at CircuitRise, it wasn't uncommon for him to make visits to the shipping yard to oversee company operations.”

Lucita Azaro

“His name is Alexei Radovic. On paper, he's a political officer, but in reality, he's a known spy from Lespia stationed at their consulate in Zille."

Lucita Azaro

“He has diplomatic immunity, so we've been unable to bring him in for questioning."

Narrator

A silence fell over the room as we all absorbed the news.

Player_Romus

“What would motivate Lespia to take such actions?”

Lucita Azaro

“My guess is that the bombing was meant to sow discord between Rizia and Wehlen, with the ultimate goal of destabilizing both regimes."

Player_Romus

“Alvarez, that sneak. I knew he couldn't be trusted."

Lucita Azaro

“Going public with the Lespia evidence will be good insurance, even if it's not strictly needed."

Titus Gordion

“With all that in mind, I suggest reviewing the contingency plan we made for the return of Zille in lieu of an agreement with Wehlen."

Player_Romus

“Agreed. Let us explore our options.”

Lucita Azaro

“The way I see it, we can either approach this diplomatically or, if necessary, take a more... *aggressive* stance.”

Player_Romus

“Let's begin with the diplomatic approach. Thoughts?”

Lucita Azaro

“While we don't have a lot of options, we could continue supporting ATA."

Lucita Azaro

“We still have Su Omina at our disposal. Further support of their operations could be an effective option."

Lucita Azaro

“More importantly, Rizia's military capabilities have also significantly grown under your rule."

“So what are your thoughts on Su Omina and ATA's activities?"
